# Simple Alarm Clock #

This is a simple python code that functions as an alarm clock. it allows the Users to set the desired time for the user to be notified. Alarm time is set in 12-hours format and it gives users to select between AM and PM. The code will continuously check the current time, and when the set time is reached, it will play an alarm sound.

# Getting Started 

Prerequisites
Make sure you have Python installed on your machine. You can download Python from <https//:python.org>

# Installation 

Clone the repository to your local machine:

bash
Copy code
git clone <https://github.com/kincaidson1/Simple-Alarm-Clock>
Navigate to the project directory:

bash
Copy code
cd Simple-Alarm-Clock
Usage
Run the script:

bash
Copy code
python alarm_clock.py
Follow the on-screen prompts to set the alarm hour, minute, and choose AM or PM.

Once the alarm time is reached, the script will play an alarm sound. You can adjust the alarm sound file path in the script if needed.

The script will print "Alarm ringing........" during the alarm and "Alarm stopped" after the alarm has finished ringing.

# Customization

Feel free to customize the script to fit your needs. You can change the alarm sound file, modify the sleep duration between time checks, or make any other adjustments to suit your preferences.

